aker type skele's, gorillas, and hornets.  Maybe it's just bad luck but it's taking me twice the time to get the same amount of exp lately, and it's not because I gained a lvl.  So to answer your questions...<br><br>Yes, avoid sarnaks.  Skele's and apes are good, hornets too if you got PoL and Voltic Draught (they resist fire).  There are a couple undead ruins that have only skele's and gor's, but unless you plan on parking your ass and killing only what pops at the ruins then you're just gonna have to run around and avoid the sarnaks.  I'd recommend the ruins that's just north east of the giant fort.  The area between the fort and that ruins is pretty safe to quad.  Only mob I seen wandering around there is Guller.<br><br>There are better places to quad, but BW is good if you don't play much cause it's almost always wide open.  But then again the reason it's wide open is because there are better places to hunt.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwizardzapinsommaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wizard Zapin Sommaz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/9/02 1:39:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/Zapin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Burning Woods?</span><hr size=1> I actually quadded there quite a bit and xp is decent and mobs blow up fairly well.  Just make sure you drag Gullerback close to a zoneline before trying to solo him since it can be hard to tell whether he will summon or not before you damage him.  Currently I prefer The Grey since pulls are fast since if you hunt in the right spot all are blue and xp is better. <p><embed src="http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/Zapin1.swf" width="280" height="160" quality="best" type="application/x-shockwave-flash"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uussul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ussul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/9/02 9:34:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Burning Woods?</span><hr size=1> Gullerback is heavily MR and resisted every attempt I made to root/snare him. If you get him on you, zone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwizardzapinsommaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wizard Zapin Sommaz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/12/02 1:01:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/Zapin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Burning Woods?</span><hr size=1> Bah as long as he is not summoning he is not too bad if you have the mana.  Just do not bother trying to snare or root and just run like hell (with SoW not JBoots or runspeed) and blast him with ice. <p><embed src="http://www.allcanadiantrees.com/eq/Zapin1.swf" width="280" height="160" quality="best" type="application/x-shockwave-flash"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right 